    # We divide n by the smallest prime factor until it is no longer divisible

    # We continue this until n is a prime number itself, which will be the largest prime factor
    largest_prime = -1
    # Check for divisibility by 2

            n = n // i
    # If n is a prime number greater than 2
    if n > 2:
        largest_prime = n
    return largest_prime
